&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 18pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Warehouse Management System Consultant (NetSuite)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EMEA, UK Based (Remote, must be based in the UK)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(186, 55, 42);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We exist to transform our customers and change lives&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We’re Looking For&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Are you ready to take on a dynamic role where you can make a real impact? As a WMS Consultant at RF-SMART, you&#39;ll be at the forefront of delivering cutting-edge warehouse management solutions using our innovative data collection software for NetSuite ERP. With a broad understanding of general warehouse operations, best practices and business processes, the consultant will lead our implementations, and support our expanding customer base in the EMEA region.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design &amp;amp; Deliver:&lt;/strong&gt; Create tailored warehouse data collection solutions using RF-SMART for the NetSuite ERP application, focusing on areas like receiving, inventory control, picking, and light production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consult &amp;amp; Advise:&lt;/strong&gt; Be the go-to expert for customers, guiding them on best practices in warehouse setup, receiving, and shipping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Customer Implementations:&lt;/strong&gt; Perform tasks and assist customers with application design, setup, testing and training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem-Solve: &lt;/strong&gt;Tackle customer issues head-on, whether through the NetSuite ERP or RF-SMART software, and find innovative solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assume Role of Trusted Advisor:&lt;/strong&gt; Comfortable as primary contact to provide product information and best practice solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enhance &amp;amp; Innovate: &lt;/strong&gt;Scope and document custom requirements, conduct thorough testing of developed solutions, coordinate with the development team to ensure successful, on-target delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stay Organized: &lt;/strong&gt;Keep all customer interactions, project tasks, and communications organized and on track in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Train &amp;amp; Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead training sessions and provide ongoing support, ensuring customers are confident and successful post-Go Live&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typically, five (5) or more years of warehouse operational experience, or warehouse consulting, with familiarity with ERP systems (especially NetSuite) considered a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience delivering projects successfully, from kickoff through Go-Live, while managing timelines, scope, and customer expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A clear, confident communicator with excellent written, verbal, and presentation skills, whether in person or through remote meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible and willing to travel throughout the EMEA region as required to support customer implementations, training, and meetings. Travel is expected to be around 30%, though this may vary depending on project needs.&lt;/li&gt;
